name: places/ChIJCxKQYWUR2jERg785Atz6Agk/reviews/ChZDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnTUR3bU5tRVNBEAE
text: {'text': 'Went for an early lunch.\nPlace was almost empty aside from 2 and a half full tables. We got seated at the same table (there was a sauce divider in the middle) as another group of 2...which wasnt great. They left before us but it was really disruptive to have the waiter clean the table while we were still eating on one side. Keep in mind there is a dining time limit so it\'s best to decide what you want, before you get seated.\nWe got the "A5 wagyu karubi and rosu 100g" set ($20.90) and the A5 wagyu misuji and US karubi 100g" set ($22.90) with 150g rice each. Ordered an extra 50g "Pork belly" ($4.50). Portion size for a set is definitely not enough for one person, so be prepared to possibly order extra food. The meat itself was yummy. They are thin, so it\'s very easy to overcook it. The rice portion comes in 3 different sizes with no extra charge, we went with the smallest size which was enough for us.', 'languageCode': 'en'}

name: places/ChIJCxKQYWUR2jERg785Atz6Agk/reviews/ChZDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnTURRak5yUFV3EAE
text: {'text': 'Fuss free casual Japanese chain restaurant with good taste and the quality matches the friendly prices.  Popular with solo diners or families. Easy to diy and serve yourself a good grilled meat meal without the trouble to clean up, thanks to their kind staff who is there to assist you.\nTheir sauces and bonito seaweed rice is delicious. Meat quality is quite good, especially for their A4 Wagyu.', 'languageCode': 'en'}
